I think this is very interesting (and sitting at my workplace right now, oh my god, we take security so seriously here) and very relatable. It’s well executed, but I’m struggling as a reader to understand the last log and it’s significance. You may need to be blunter here; Scp articles do not lend themselves particularly well to subtlety.








Living the dream, or dreaming the life?






